Purpose
-------
Implement the Online Book Catalogue Protocol using TCP sockets.


Compilation
-----------
Execute "make" in the root directory.


Usage
-----
Start the server with "./server {port_number}" to bind it to a specific
port. Start one or more clients in separate terminals with 
"./client {server_address} {port_number}".


Known Limitations
-----------------
- Server cannot accept a single newline as input.
- Maximum size client request and server response is 1024 characters.


References
----------
- With permission, used socket client and server code given by Dave 
  OHallaron at Carnegie Mellon University.
